.TH "hfi1_rc_verbs_aborted" 9 "hfi1_rc_verbs_aborted" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hfi1_rc_verbs_aborted \- handle abort status
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" hfi1_rc_verbs_aborted
.BI "(struct rvt_qp *qp "  ","
.BI "struct hfi1_opa_header *opah "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "qp" 12
the QP
.IP "opah" 12
the opa header
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This code modifies both ACK bit in BTH[2]
and the s_flags to go into send one mode.

This serves to throttle the send engine to only
send a single packet in the likely case the
a link has gone down.
